'''''Shards and Swords''''' was a play penned by an anonymous playwright sometime in or before [[163 DR]].

{{quote|''[[Thieves]]? Ah, such an ugly word... think of them instead as kings-in-training. Ye seem upset, even disputatious. Well, then, look upon them as the most honest sort of merchant.''|Excerpt from ''Shards and Swords''}}
